			<div class="comment-content"><p>Interesting. It could be that time is the way to do this. E.g., if &#8220;point reader interpretation&#8221; was replacing &#8220;evidence found&#8221; <em>within</em> some semi-thematic subset of the corpus, thinking article-by-article would be misleading. Both topics would be associated with the same articles, in a sense. (Let&#8217;s say, articles that are kind of argue-y or epistemolog-ish.) But they&#8217;d be negatively correlated over time. Cool lead, anyway.</p>
</div>

