			<div class="comment-content"><p>On philology and linguistics, a data point. I ran a Google ngram query on <a href="http://books.google.com/ngrams/graph?content=philology%2Clinguistics&amp;year_start=1850&amp;year_end=2000&amp;corpus=15&amp;smoothing=1&amp;share=" rel="nofollow">&#8220;philology&#8221; and &#8220;linguistics&#8221; (smoothing = 1)</a> from 1850 to 2000. &#8220;Philology&#8221; is pretty flat the whole period, but a bit higher from 1860 to 1895. &#8220;Linguistics&#8221; starts at the bottom and comes up rapidly after 1950, peaks a bit after 1970, and then tapers off.</p>
</div>

