			<div class="comment-content"><p>On the question of periodization, I don&#8217;t disagree with the renewed emphasis on continuity. But I&#8217;d add that small and/or gradual shifts aren&#8217;t a priori incompatible with models of punctuated equilibrium. Sometimes small absolute differences really matter. And then there&#8217;s what Marx or Jameson would call the reality of the illusion; standing narratives about eras and schools affect the kinds of work we do, even when they don&#8217;t line up with the objects they&#8217;re supposed to organize.</p>
<p>But none of this is to disagree with the original point, which was that we&#8217;re getting a much better feel for the kinds and magnitudes of changes that have happened in past literature and scholarship. W00t!</p>
</div>

