			<div class="comment-content"><p>@Scott and Matthew. Yes.</p>
<p>Back in the middle 70s Rene Thom made a splash with catastrophe theory, which was quickly swamped by chaos and complex dynamics. Catastrophe theory is about how gradual continuous change can, under certain circumstances, have discontinuous manifestations. I recently saw an application to the 2008 financial collapse and other things: <a href="http://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/10/08/dangerous-intersection/" rel="nofollow">http://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/10/08/dangerous-intersection/</a></p>
